==English==

===Etymology===
The name Polynesia comes from the Greek words poly (many) and nesos (islands).  According to link below, "the term Polynesia was coined by Charles de Brosses in 1756 and applied to all the Pacific islands.  The present restricted use was proposed by Dumont d'Urville during a famous lecture at the Geographical Society in Paris in 1831."

